.TH "KZ-POST-MIGRATE" "1" "4.2.1" "kz" "User commands"

.SH NAME
kz-post-migrate - post-migration helper script for after migrating to Linux

.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY kz-post-migrate
.YS

.SH DESCRIPTION
After migrating to Linux, look for Windows-specific files [1] and delete them.
.br
The search starts in the current directory and includes all subdirectories.
.br
First the files are searched for and displayed, then there is the option to
delete them.

[1]
Files with names (case insensitive) matching the following patterns are
considered Windows-specific:
.br
    ~*
.br
    *.bat
.br
    *.exe
.br
    *.lnk
.br
    desktop.ini
.br
    thumbs.db


.SH KZ
Part of the \fBkz\fR(1) package.
